## Release Permissions

GitHub repository settings required:
- **Workflow permissions**: "Read and write permissions"
- **Allow GitHub Actions to**: "create and approve pull requests" ✓

## CI Pipeline Best Practices

### Pipeline Optimization
- Cache pnpm dependencies for faster builds
- Run tests in parallel when possible
- Use matrix builds for multiple Node.js versions
- Fail fast on critical validation errors

### Environment Management
- Use development environment for CI testing
- Deploy to production only on release tags
- Separate environment secrets management
- Maintain consistent environment variables

### Error Handling
- Capture and report detailed error logs
- Use appropriate exit codes for different failure types
- Provide clear error messages for common failures
- Include debugging information in CI outputs

### Security Practices
- Use least-privilege access tokens
- Secure handling of environment secrets
- Validate all external dependencies
- Audit CI/CD pipeline configurations regularly

## Workflow Examples

### Basic Validation Workflow
```yaml
name: Validate Code
on: [push, pull_request]
jobs:
  validate:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    steps:
      - uses: actions/checkout@v4
      - name: Setup pnpm
        uses: pnpm/action-setup@v2
        with:
          version: 8
      - name: Setup Node.js
        uses: actions/setup-node@v4
        with:
          node-version: '20'
          cache: 'pnpm'
      - run: pnpm install --frozen-lockfile
      - run: pnpm type-check
      - run: pnpm test:run
```

### Release Workflow
```yaml
name: Release
on:
  push:
    branches: [main]
jobs:
  release:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    permissions:
      contents: write
      issues: write
      pull-requests: write
    steps:
      - uses: actions/checkout@v4
        with:
          fetch-depth: 0
      - name: Setup pnpm
        uses: pnpm/action-setup@v2
        with:
          version: 8
      - name: Setup Node.js
        uses: actions/setup-node@v4
        with:
          node-version: '20'
          cache: 'pnpm'
      - run: pnpm install --frozen-lockfile
      - run: pnpm test:run
      - run: npx semantic-release
        env:
          GITHUB_TOKEN: ${{ secrets.GITHUB_TOKEN }}
```

